<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key: A major (3 sharps). Long hymn (32 bars) with rich harmonic variety.
- Non-diatonic subs: Eb/D# → E (⑤); F#7 → F#m (⑥m); G#m treated as C#m extended (shares G#).
- "F natural" in bar 28 annotation → F#m (⑥m) diatonic sub.
- Opening (bars 1-4): sparse "33" and "43" voicings in LH — wide spacing, light RH thirds.
- Bars 5-8: Richer — AΔ7 and E7 7th chords; LH builds to 4 notes; RH approaches G#5.
- Bars 9-12: Full quarter-note LH motion (4 chords/bar 10 and 12); E7→A resolution.
- Bars 13-16: Repeat of opening melody with varied voicings (AΔ7, "43" 1st inv).
- Bars 17-20: New phrase — quartal "44" on A (A2 D3 G#3), F#° → E sub.
- Bars 21-24: Climax region — C#m→F#m→E dominant pedal (bar 24: E held both halves).
- Bars 25-26: D→A motion repeated; RH F#5 highest note (bar 26).
- Bars 27-28: F#m→Bm fourth relationship; bar 28 F-natural → F#m diatonic sub.
- Bars 29-32: Final sweep — same E→A→D→A circle; RH climbs to F#5 (bar 30); Bm7→A final cadence.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 10 RH descent E5→E5→D5→C#5 over LH bass A2→E2→D2→A2 — parallel contrary motion.
- Bar 18 RH descent G#5→E5→C#5→B4 mirrors inner voice of E→C#m→F#m→Bm progression.
- Bar 24 dominant pedal: E held in both LH halves — harmonic stability before final section.
- Bar 32 E→A approach: classical V→I with E2 bass supporting final A tonic.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-4: Sparse (3-4 note LH, 2-note RH), half-note values — quiet, reflective opening.
- Bars 5-8: Growing (AΔ7, E7 7th chords) — harmonic color increasing.
- Bars 9-16: Middle section — quarter-note LH motion at peak activity (bars 10, 18).
- Bars 17-24: Varied texture — quartal voicing, climax in bars 22 and 31.
- Bars 25-32: Final broad sweep — D major subdominant sections provide breadth; quiet close.
-->
